com.bluegosling.apt.reflect

Class ArProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
      • com.bluegosling.apt.AbstractProcessor
        • com.bluegosling.apt.reflect.ArProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Processor

    public abstract class ArProcessor
extends AbstractProcessor
    An abstract annotation processor whose methods is defined in terms of the reflection-like API in this package instead of the standard element and type mirror APIs.

        protected final boolean doProcess(Set<? extends TypeElement> annotations,
                                  RoundEnvironment env)
        Translates the given element and round environment into reflection-like types and then delegates to process(Set).
        Specified by:
        doProcess in class AbstractProcessor
        Parameters:
        annotations - annotations that the processor supports
        env - information about this round of processing
        Returns:
        true if the processor claims the annotations, false otherwise
        See Also:

      • process

        protected abstract boolean process(Set<ArClass> annotationTypes)
        Processes annotations. This does the work of the processor. The supplied types are the annotation types that this processor supports and that were encountered during the round of compilation/processing. Implementations can use the round environment to query for annotated elements.
        Parameters:
        annotationTypes - the annotation types to process
        Returns:
        true if the processor claims the annotations, false otherwise
